result.name: Café de Coral

reviews.text: Much choice and reasonable price. Very busy and not very accommodated.
Space is a bit crowded and have a mouldy smell, guess the air conditioning system is dirty and humid. Tables and floors are not too clean. Overall OK for a quick bite.
Food quality is good, get your bang for the buck if you will ! However finding a place to sit after you picked up your food was a struggle !!

Cafe de Coral is the only place in Hong Kong that serves beef curry that's closest to the preparation from my home country, Bangladesh.
They had altered it to Nanyang curry in the meantime but are back to their usual preparation now.
For new visitors, the ordering process is simple. You choose from a menu displayed at the entrance, order, pay with either cash or octopus (they don't accept credit cards) and queue up for your food along with your voucher. Breakfast and afternoon tea has local foods like bread, eggs, sausage, congee, tea and local drinks.
Offers a good selection. Food was ok. People preparing the orders should learn more about "good & friendly service" from the old lady cleaning the tables

result.name: 大家樂

reviews.text: 在那裡打边爐🔥價錢唔貴但食材尙算新鮮。
食物也可以😋
雖然旺角呢間店幾時都咁多人，但員工服務好有人情味！ 🤩
4月份某天中午時分，我在大家樂買Lunch外賣，回到公司才發現該快餐店的一個員工沒有將飯放入外賣盒內!由於我沒有時間再折回大家樂，有朋友見况幫我在附近餐廳買咗一個白飯，才解決咗!事後我將實況告知該快餐集團主管，該集團主管多次來電道歉，並表示誠意，寄咗两張餐券給我!值得讚許!
定期有新產品，但有時候味道比較不同，可能師傅5同有5同的效果
